Chile Won’t Need New or Higher Taxes for 2012 Budget: Longueira

-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 
2011-09-27T13:30:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/chile-won-t-need-new-or-higher-taxes-for-2012-budget-longueira.html
Chile’s government won’t need new
or higher taxes to finance plans to increase spending by 5
percent next year, Economy Minister Pablo Longueira told
reporters today at a forum in Santiago.  The budget proposal will be presented to Congress on Sept.
29, Longueira said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
